The Telegraph - Calcutta
 BCCI contracts likely before July
Bangalore: The BCCI is on the verge of finalising a contract payment system for players which is likely to be introduced before the Asia Cup in July. Its almost final. We have completed discussions. The documentation process (for the agreement) is in progress. Its likely to be introduced before the Asia Cup in July, BCCI secretary, S.K. Nair said on Monday. Players have more or less accepted the conditions and a final meeting will be called before inking the pact, Nair added. Singapores plans The Singapore Cricket Association (SCA) is planning to host a tournament this year involving Australia and India, adds a report from Singapore. The aim of the tournament is to promote the sport in the region, SCA president Kiran Deshpande said. We are looking to organise an international event in this calendar year and will get a clearer picture in a couple of months. We are still in the process of identifying which countries can suit our schedule. Given a choice, we are looking at some big countries like India and Australia.  (AGENCIES)  Copyright 
